tags.name: Version
tags.description:
Any time Addepar makes changes to the API that are not backward-compatible, we will release a new version. This API version number must be included in the API URL.

For backward-compatible changes to the API, Addepar will provide a new patch version via the API.

Current API Version

The current version is v1.16

tags.name: Arguments
tags.description:
This route provides read-only access to attribute arguments, primarily such that they are discoverable
for use in v1 Portfolio Query API.

Argument list is not every available argument in Addepar, but rather is whitelisted based on what v1 Portfolio Query API supports.

tags.name: Attributes
tags.description: This route provides read-only access to attributes, primarily such that they are discoverable for use in v1 Portfolio Query API.

tags.name: Archived Files
tags.description: This route provides access to V1 Files that have been marked as deleted or otherwise known as archived. There are slight differences, including a deleted_at field, from the traditional File JSON object, but these differences don't change the object or represent a copy. These fields have been omitted and non-pertinent from the v1/files routes.

tags.name: Groups
tags.description: The Groups API can be used to create and delete groups in Addepar, as well as retrieve and update group details.

tags.name: Group Types
tags.description:
Group Types are categorical metadata that are attached to Groups. Group Types, like the rest of the V1 routes, follow the JSON API specification.

- `group_type_key`: A unique identifier for the group type within your firm. This is in sync with the id.

- `display_name`: A user facing display name which is used as a label for grouping of groups of similar type.

- `is_permissioned_resource` : A boolean flag which determines if groups of this type are a permissioned resource.

- A permissioned resource can be granted directly to a user - These groups also grant access to the group members.

- A non permissioned resource cannot be granted directly to a user - Access to these groups is granted by checking for access to all the group members.

tags.name: Jobs
tags.description:
The asynchronous Jobs API allows you to reliably export large sets of analysis data and download the results any time within 24 hours of the initial request.

More specifically, the Jobs API allows you to:

- Issue API requests that cannot be completed within the current, synchronous API timeout limits
- Avoid maintaining an open HTTP connection while waiting for a response from the API
- Protect long-running API requests from the effects of unreliable networks

tags.name: Portfolio
tags.description: The Portfolio API makes it easy to export data for a specific portfolio based on a saved analysis or transactions view in Addepar.

tags.name: Roles
tags.description: The Roles API can be used to view roles created by your firm, as well as add or remove the users assigned to each role.

tags.name: Users
tags.description: The Users API can be used to view, create, and delete users. You can also update user information, tool permissions, and portfolio access.
